From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 20:16:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix GET->POST and add validator checks from BRK-PB comparison
 findings

Critical fix: execute_sparql now uses POST instead of GET. GET fails with
HTTP 431 once a query (e.g. a large VALUES clause) pushes the querystring
past ~30-40KB/~300-500 URIs; POST is confirmed to handle ~255KB/3000 URIs
without issues.

Other fixes from the rijksmonumenten vs. Kadaster BRK-PB comparison run:
- validate_sparql now warns on ORDER BY + OPTIONAL (causes a consistent
  HTTP 504 on this endpoint, even with a small LIMIT) and recommends the
  two-stage subquery workaround.
- validate_sparql now warns on 2+ independent OPTIONAL blocks in one query
  (silent Cartesian product between unrelated multi-valued relations).
- validate_sparql now warns when ceo:huisnummer/ceo:perceelnummer are used
  with a bare numeric literal -- both are untyped string literals in this
  data, so an unquoted number silently matches nothing.
- classify_error now also classifies by raw HTTP 504 status (a gateway
  timeout body often doesn't contain the word "timeout").
- Added an "identifiers" semantics topic documenting the huisnummer/
  perceelnummer string-literal gotcha.
- Documented the endpoint's apparent query-result caching behavior and a
  confirmed source-data duplicate-triple issue (116x repeat on one
  monument) in CAPABILITIES.md and the workflow instructions.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
